column2: The Jarvis turbine discharge was reduced from full output (about 1850 cfs) back down to the Operating Diagram discharge of 1000 cfs at 6:12 PM as directed by the Canal Corporation because the flood risk declined.
The Jarvis turbine release was increased to its capability (1850 cfs) at 6:30 pm to help reduce the flood potential.
The Mohawk Valley Water Authority estimated withdrawal for May 9 is 28 cfs.
As of May 1 the elevation trigger became ACTIVATED and Routine Communications Protocols have been utilized.

Jarvis under discharged 157 cfsd on Feb 26 & 27 as a result of a weather related transmission constraint.  This water is being made up by increasing the Jarvis Operating Diagram release of 670 cfs  to 716 cfs for the 82 hours beginning 2pm Mar 1 until midnight on Mar 4.
